org.nasdanika.html.emf

Interface EObjectActionResolver

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, BiConsumer<EObjectActionResolver.Context,ProgressMonitor>, Consumer<EObjectActionResolver.Context>, Diagnosable, ExecutionParticipant, ExecutionParticipantInfo
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EObjectActionBuilder.EObjectActionResolverAdapter

    public interface EObjectActionResolver
extends Consumer<EObjectActionResolver.Context>
    Marker interface for adapters attached to actions created by EObjectActionBuilder instances. This interface is used to perform action configuration which requires action cross-referencing such as linking from one action to another. Resolver's execute() is invoked after all actions are created and the action hierarchy is established. Parameter function provides mapping of semantic elements to actions created during the adapter execution phase and collected by the registry.
    Author:
    Pavel
